message.content:
Analysis of the Target Image
----------------------------

From the picture, there are two separate “structures”:

1) Left‐hand “Rocket”‐like Tower  
   • Central Core: One tall orange cylinder.  
   • Middle “Ring”: Four short blue rectangular blocks arranged in a ring around the cylinder’s mid‐section.  
   • Base Wedges: Four orange wedge‐shaped blocks, each leaning outward at the base.  
   • Top “Roof”: One orange triangular‐prism block resting on top of the cylinder.

   Visually it stacks in (roughly) three layers:  
   – Bottom layer: The four orange wedges around the base.  
   – Mid layer: The central cylinder (running bottom to top) plus the ring of four blue blocks around it.  
   – Top layer: A single triangular prism.  

2) Right‐hand “Two‐Column” Structure  
   • Base: One long yellow rectangular block lying flat on the ground.  
   • Columns: Two tall orange cylinders standing on the base.  
   • Top Beam: Another long yellow rectangular block resting on the two columns.  
   • Roof Piece: An orange triangular‐prism block on top of the upper yellow beam.

   This can be seen as (roughly) three or four layers:  
   – Bottom layer: The horizontal yellow block on the ground.  
   – Middle layer: Two vertical orange cylinders.  
   – Upper layer: The horizontal yellow block.  
   – Very top: The orange triangular prism “roof.”  

Block‐Dictionary Matching
-------------------------

Matching each visible piece to the dictionary (without rotating any block differently from its dictionary orientation) gives:

• Tall orange cylinder (vertical) → Block #6  
• Short blue rectangular block (lying “flat”) → Block #2  
• Orange triangular prism with its triangular faces to the front/back → Block #11  
• Four orange wedges, each in a distinct orientation so they can lean outward around the cylinder → Blocks #13, #14, #15, and #16  
• Long yellow rectangular block (horizontal) → Block #5  

Hence the final parts‐list is:

Left Tower  
• 1 × #6 (center cylinder)  
• 4 × #2 (blue ring blocks)  
• 4 × (#13, #14, #15, #16) (wedge blocks)  
• 1 × #11 (top roof prism)

Right Columns  
• 2 × #5 (yellow horizontal blocks, top and bottom)  
• 2 × #6 (orange columns)  
• 1 × #11 (orange triangular prism)

Step‐by‐Step Assembly
---------------------

Use the following move/placement sequence (15 total moves) to build both structures:

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 6   // place the tall orange cylinder (left tower center)
  Step2:  Move block with index 2   // first blue block around mid‐cylinder
  Step3:  Move block with index 2   // second blue block
  Step4:  Move block with index 2   // third blue block
  Step5:  Move block with index 2   // fourth blue block
  Step6:  Move block with index 13  // first orange wedge at the base
  Step7:  Move block with index 14  // second orange wedge at the base
  Step8:  Move block with index 15  // third orange wedge
  Step9:  Move block with index 16  // fourth orange wedge
  Step10: Move block with index 11  // orange triangular prism on top of cylinder

  Step11: Move block with index 5   // bottom yellow horizontal block (right structure)
  Step12: Move block with index 6   // first orange cylinder as column
  Step13: Move block with index 6   // second orange cylinder as column
  Step14: Move block with index 5   // top yellow horizontal block
  Step15: Move block with index 11  // orange triangular prism roof
}
